In this statement, the President acknowledges Yom HaShoah, a day of remembrance for the Holocaust. He expresses solidarity with people of all faiths in the United States, Israel, and worldwide, in honoring the six million Jews and all victims of Nazi brutality. The President highlights the importance of remembering those who perished and the opportunity to honor survivors who rebuilt their lives. He mentions his upcoming address at the Shoah Foundation and emphasizes the need to oppose anti-Semitism and ensure that the atrocities of the Holocaust are never repeated.